column28: model_relations_comment
Lines LU-134-A and LU-134-B have been shown to be related (RIKEN).
LC-1F (Floating variant) is from the same patient as LC-1-sq (Lung Cancer-1/Squamous). ;LC-1-sq-SF is a variant of LC-1-sq cultured in serum-free media (RIKEN).
NCI-H125 and NCI-H513 have been show to be cross contaminated (ATCC, ICLAC)
LB647-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB647-SCLC.
PC-14 has been shown to be a derivitive of PC-9 (RIKEN, ECACC).
SBC-1 and SBC-2 exhibit the same DNA profile (JCRB).
COR-L23-R is a multi-drug resistant sub-line derived from the parent line COR-L23 after treatment with doxorubicin (ECACC).
NCI-H1870 and NCI-H1304 are known syonymous lines (ICLAC).
NCI-H1819 and the matched normal line NCI-BL1819 were derived from the same patient as NCI-H1693 following chemotherapy. (PMID: 8806092)
NCI-BL2141 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2141 (ATCC).
NCI-H1876 & NCI-H1882 & NCI-H1881 have been derived from the same same patient. (NCI-Navy Medical Oncology Brance Cell Line Supplement DOI: 10.1002/jcb.240630505)
NCI-BL1437 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1437. (ATCC)
NCI-BL2087 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2087 (ATCC).
NCI-BL209 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H209 (ATCC).
NCI-BL2171 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2171 (ATCC).
NCI-BL2347 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2347 (ATCC).
NCI-BL2009 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2009 (ATCC).

The human umbilical vein cell line, EA.hy926, was established by fusing primary human umbilical vein cells with a thioguanine-resistant clone of A549 by exposure to polyethylene glycol (PEG). Hybrid clones were selected in HAT medium and screened for factor VIII-related antigen. (ATCC)
HCC-827-GR5 is a Gefitinib resistant clone of HCC-827. (10.1126/science.1141478).
RERF-LC-MA has the same DNA profile as lung squamous carcinoma cell line SK-MES-1 (JCRB).
